Preheat your #oven{} to 190°C/170°C fan/gas mark 5.

Halve, core and finely chop the @Pears{1%unit}.

In a #bowl{}, mix the @Vanilla Cake Batter{1%pouch}, @Ground Cinnamon{1%sachet} and chopped pear.

Line an #oven dish{approx 15x20cm} and pop the batter into it.

Bake the cake in the oven until it's firm to touch and a #skewer{} inserted comes out clean, ~{45-50%minutes}.

Once cooked, set aside to cool completely.

Meanwhile, add the @Cream Cheese{50%grams} and @Sugar{2%tsp} to a bowl.

Whisk vigorously until smooth, ~{1%minute}.

Once cooled, transfer the cake to a #plate{} or #serving board{}.

Place the cream cheese frosting in a #piping bag{} and drizzle over the cake (you can also use a #freezer bag{} with a small incision in one of the corners).

Or, if you prefer, simply spoon the frosting on top.

> A cinnamon-spiced delight that's soft and spongey with a festive feeling.